OL,3,GLondon & South East
OL,4,
OL,5,CThis Evening and Tonight:FIsolated
OL,6,Fshowers soon dying away, with some
OL,7,Flate sunny spells for many. Cloud
OL,8,Famounts should increase from the east
OL,9,Ffor a time overnight, perhaps bringing
OL,10,Fthe odd spot of light rain. Chilly,
OL,11,Fperhaps with local rural grass frost.
OL,12,
OL,13,CTuesday:FEarly cloud largely clearing
OL,14,Fwestwards to leave a mainly fine day
OL,15,Fwith sunny spells. Temperatures near-
OL,16,Fnormal, tempered by the strengthening
OL,17,Feasterly wind, especially in coastal
OL,18,Fdistricts.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
